  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposal fails to provide sufficient external amenity space which is deemed as private, usable and safe for a 2 bedroom and studio flat. Therefore, the proposal fails to comply with BP5 of the Borough Wide Development Plan&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;Whilst the increase of one unit to the housing stock would be supported, it would lead to the loss of a dwellinghouse which has the potential to be a family sized dwellinghouse.&amp;nbsp;The Local Policies seek for new housing to be flexible for future user’s. Therefore, by previously approving application 19/01413/FUL for a double storey side extension, this is a good example of how existing stock can be adapted and expanded to meet current housing needs within the Borough.&amp;nbsp;It has been highlighted in the local SHMA that family sized dwellinghouse&#x27;s (3+ bedrooms) need to be preserved, therefore Local Planning Policies protect the loss of a family sized dwellinghouse. Therefore, the need to preserve the number of family sized dwellinghouse&#x27;s outweighs the need for smaller sized units.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;NPPF&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt; Policies H9 and H10 of the Draft London Plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;Policy SP 3 and DMH 4 of the Draft Local Plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;Policy CM1 and CM2 of the Core Strategy DPD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt; Policy BP10 and BC4&amp;nbsp;of the Borough Wide DPD.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The proposed development would&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;result in a greater concentration of irregular comings and goings in relation to its surrounding properties.&amp;nbsp; The proposal would generate more waste, noise and general disturbance than a single dwellinghouse, which would have a&amp;nbsp; negative impact on&amp;nbsp; neighbouring amenity and in turn the standard of living of neighbouring residents&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The proposal is therefore contrary to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;- National Planning Policy Framework (MHCLG, February 2019);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;- Policies BP8 and BP11 of the LDF Borough Wide Development Plan Policies DPD (March 2011);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;- The Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;- Policies SP7, DMD1 and DMSI3 of the Draft Local Plan (Regulation 19 Consultation version, October 2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:20px;margin-right:20px;margin-top:0px;&quot;&gt;The double storey side extension approved under planning application 19/01413/FUL was approved to compliment and increase the size of the application site to convert it into a three bedroom dwellinghouse. However, the proposed conversion of the dwellinghouse into two self contained flats is materially different to the proposal in 19/0413/FUL. Furthermore, the proposed first floor balcony would overlook the corner of Grafton Avenue and the public realm. As balconies are not a common form of development on Grafton Avenue and within the Becontree Estate, the balcony would be of an incongruent design and would not have regard to the form and function of the surrounding area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As such, the proposed development is contrary to:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;National Planning Policy Framework (MHCLG, February 2019)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Policy D1,&amp;nbsp; and D4 of the London Plan (March 2021)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Policies BP11 of the LDF Borough Wide Development Plan Policies DPD (March 2011)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Policies SP2 and DMD1 of the Draft Local Plan (Regulation 19 October 2020)&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
